What are Walk-In Cooler and Freezer Combos?
Walk-In Cooler and Freezer Combos are integrated refrigeration units designed for commercial and industrial foodservice applications, providing separate but connected compartments for chilling and freezing within a single structure. These systems are essential for operations requiring efficient storage of both perishable goods at cool temperatures (typically between 35°F to 38°F) and frozen products (at or below 0°F). They are commonly constructed from insulated panels often using polyurethane foam cores with metal skins and feature robust refrigeration systems, doors, and shelving configurations tailored to high-volume use.

